  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Media Support  Year 1</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">- Four private Media houses
- New/innovative medias (through a grant mechanism)
- Journalists, online bloggers and newsroom editorial teams
- National audiences in Burundi (radio listeners, readers, online followers)</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Media Support (MS) project (2018-2021), entitled &apos;Disseminating facts, enhancing synergies and rebuilding trust through Burundian media&apos;, represents the third consecutive period of funding for private (independent) media houses in Burundi since 2014. The current Media Support project aims to continue to assist, develop and professionalize the private media landscape in Burundi thereby promoting the production of complementary, pluralistic information. As such, it seeks to
- Build the capacity of four private media houses at the editorial, structural and financial level 
- Create an innovation space, through a transparent journalism grant mechanism
- Facilitate synergised and co-produced programs to disseminate factual and reliable information to Burundian citizens;
- Strengthen existing and new social media tools and platforms to ensure citizens participation in media productions.
- Sensitize the Burundian media and public to recognize and resist dangerous and hateful speeches broadcast online and offline, by broadcasting countering media productions.
The project is implemented by Radio La Benevolencija (RLB) Humanitarian Tools Foundation in partnership with RNW Media.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The overall objective of the MS project is to facilitate pluralistic information production and dissemination that contributes to reducing social, political and ethnic polarization and creates resilience in the Burundian population against misinformation, manipulation and incitement to violence.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This report deals with Year 1 (2018-2019) of the 36-month Media Support project. Years 2 and 3 have a different activity code and will be reported separately.</narrative>
  </description>
